Package University

Class University

java.lang.Object
University.University
public class University extends Object
Class for a University and provides methods for managing teachers, students, departments, and programmes. Holds most of the data for the system and is the main interface for accessing it.

    • getPassword

      public String getPassword(int id)
      Gets a password by students or teachers ids from the university's list of students and teachers passwords. IDs are unique so there is no need to check if the password belongs to a student or a teacher.
      Parameters:
      id - The name of the student or teacher to retrieve.
      Returns:
      The password with the specified student or teacher id, or null if not found.

    • uniqueID

      public boolean uniqueID(int id)
      Checks if a given ID is unique among both teachers and students.
      Parameters:
      id - The ID to check for uniqueness.
      Returns:
      True if the ID is unique, false otherwise.

    • addProgramme

      public void addProgramme(Programme programme)
      Adds a programme to the list of programmes in the university. Only used temporarily when loading data from programmes.csv. For runtime programmes should be added through their department, see Department.addProgramme(Programme)
      Parameters:
      programme - The programme to be added.
